// PseudoViewer
// Center panel component that fetches a pseudo-file by path, parses it, and renders its function blocks with syntax highlighting.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

Exposes an imperative handle (PseudoViewerHandle) with scrollToFunction so the parent can programmatically scroll to a named function block.
Forwards the ref via forwardRef. Renders empty/loading/error states before main content.

FUNCTION PseudoViewer(path, project, onFunctionsChange, ref) -> JSX.Element [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  CALLS: fetchPseudoFile (pseudo-api), parsePseudo (parsePseudo)
  On path or project change, fetches file content via fetchPseudoFile; sets loading/error/content state accordingly. IF path or project is empty, clears content immediately.
  Memoizes parsePseudo(content) so re-renders without content changes are cheap.
  Notifies parent of parsed functions via onFunctionsChange whenever parsed.functions changes.
  Exposes scrollToFunction(name): queries contentRef for a [data-function="name"] element, calls scrollIntoView, and briefly adds a "function-flash" CSS class for visual feedback.
  Renders: a header bar with the file path and synced date; a module header section (title, subtitle, moduleProse); then maps parsed.functions to PseudoBlock components, passing project, currentFileStem, and an onNavigate callback that routes to /pseudo/<stem>.
